 do it in such a way that his attention is not focused directly upon his uncertainty, so that he may not be led to go into the matter and clear it up immediately.', 26164, 0), (138031, 'She is her. You are not her.', 26165, 0), (138032, 'Fiction isn''t bad. It is vital. Without commonly accepted stories about things like money, states or corporations, no complex human society can function. We can''t play football unless everyone believes in the same made-up rules, and we can''t enjoy the benefits of markets and courts without similar make-believe stories. But the stories are just tools. They should not become our goals or yardsticks. When we forget that they are mere fiction, we lose touch with reality.', 4628, 0), (138033, 'Practicing dialogue helps you to cultivate a realness that allows you to face reality on its own terms, not just the terms you’d like it to have in order to remain in your comfort zone.', 6304, 0), (138034, 'When people challenge your ideas, they help you (whether they know it or not).', 6304, 0), (138035, 'To engage in dialogue is to serve others via whatever is real inside you', 26166, 0), (138036, 'If you doubt your sanity, is that proof?', 3153, 0), (138037, 'Dialogue teaches you to listen through your emotions, not to become distracted or distanced from the truth because of them.', 6304, 0), (138038, 'Be real! Fake and phony people never grow.." - Sivaprakash Sidhu', 12584, 0), (138039, 'The memories: they are the reality.', 578, 0), (138040, 'Dialogue unplugs you from your own programming as you become more real', 26167, 0), (138041, 'Psychologically, our reality derives from the stories we tell ourselves, at least the ones we believe.', 26168, 0), (138042, 'I think maybe they come out into the grounds in nightwear. But no, in typical anorexic stype they have read the fashion magazines literally. This is their version of thin girls in strappy clothes.The girl in the petticoat talks to me, as Emma has done on occsasion, in a rather grand style, as if she is a ''lady'' of some substance and I a visiting guest.Do they chat much about clothes? I ask Emma in the car.She shakes her head.So, does she, Emma, see the difference between underwear or nightwear and ''going out'' clothes?''Yes,'' she says, her voices strained again. ''But it''s one of the things you don''t know properly when you''re ill and confused. You see these pictures and the people in the magazines are real for you.', 14675, 0), (138043, 'Dialogue is about creating awareness through self-observation; it starts from the inside out, not the outside in.', 6304, 0), (138044, 'Life is a dream. I awake it is a reality.', 2878, 0), (138045, 'Life is a reality.', 2878, 0), (138046, 'I personally feel that the universe behaves more like a song than an equation because math is about static law and music is about dynamic expression.', 7501, 0), (138047, '... he had always wondered why the sensations one felt in dreamas were so much more intense than anything one could experience in waking reality—why the horror was so total and the ecstacy so complete—and what was that extra quality which could never be recaptured afterward; the quality of what he felt when he walked down a path through tangled green leaves in a dream, in an air full of expectation, of causeless, utter rapture—and when he awakened he could not explain it, it had just been a path through some woods.', 631, 0), (138048, 'I''ve longed for you so, while my connection to the rest of reality has torn. It is that you have lost me. And I have lost you, longing for more than my enough.', 24714, 0), (138049, 'The trick, he supposed, was never to lose sight of the theoretical possibility while not for a moment taking the idea remotely seriously.', 8013, 0), (138050, 'Let each man say what he deems truth, and let truth itself be commended unto God.', 3244, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (138051, 'Dialogue isn’t a competition to be the smartest or the most correct person in the room', 26169, 0), (138052, 'We have to accept that much of reality is ineffable and so to understand it we can''t rely on words alone.', 6304, 0), (138053, 'Dialogue is an opportunity for people to communicate from outside the limitations of their points of view. When we enter a circle of dialogue, there are no labels, only human beings.', 6304, 0), (138054, 'Healing from a loss doesn''t happen on schedule.You need to give the head and heart time to catch up with the reality.', 5178, 0), (138055, 'Loving a person doesn’t make them who you desire', 26170, 0), (138056, 'That living has no value - it''s what you do with life that gives it worth.', 1584, 0), (138057, 'I neither revenge nor forgive, I just choose to ignore.', 14377, 0), (138058, 'At times, reality is love’s great challenge. When our old stories and dreams are shattered, our first instinct may be to resist, deny, or cling to the way things were. But if we loosen our grip, often what fills the space is a tender forgiveness and the potential for a new and different kind of love.', 124, 0), (138059, 'Some are imprisoned by their own perception of reality.', 11173, 0), (138060, 'It''s not about what you''re going to say, but it''s about what you''re going to do about it.', 4899, 0), (138061, 'Was 9/11 not the 20th congress of the American Dream?', 769, 0), (138062, 'You need persistence in order to maintain the reality that you desire.', 11173, 0), (138063, 'Imagination is more important than knowledge”, with due respect to Mr. Einstein, I beg to differ! “Imagination is not possible without knowledge.', 11340, 0), (138064, 'An unbearable reality, combined with the impossibility to change it, tends to lead to abstractions for abstraction''s sake, and unreality becomes more realistic than reality itself, more true, more convincing, simply because it looks at you with the eyes of justice.', 16881, 0), (138065, 'The only way to see true reality is in solitude. One of the tragedies of human existence is that reality cannot be shared. What''s real to you may not be to someone else.', 26171, 0), (138066, 'There is no such thing as, "I trust you a little or I trust you a lot." You either trust, or you do not.', 5237, 0), (138067, 'It is OK to say ''no''.It is OK to say ''I will think about it''.It is OK to say ''I will try''.It is NOT OK to make promises you cannot keep.', 4554, 0), (138068, 'Only today is real.', 24716, 0), (138069, 'Perception is more important than reality. If someone perceives something to be true, it is more important than if it is in fact true.', 26172, 0), (138070, 'Nature is sound in many forms and states of existence.', 14387, 0), (138071, 'Don''t go out of your way to correct a false assumption if it plays to your advantage.', 26172, 0), (138072, 'The world nowadays is so perverted. Some people think I''m insane only because they don''t understand my point of view.', 6342, 0), (138073, 'I would dream of a place, a place to shelter all my madness.', 5799, 0), (138074, 'sometimes even the worst dreams are better than this reality', 1916, 0), (138075, 'Truth is elusive, subtle, manysided. You know, Priscilla, there’s an old Hindu story about Truth. It seems a brash young warrior sought the hand of a beautiful princess. Her father, the king, thought he was a bit too cocksure and callow. He decreed that the warrior could only marry the princess after he had found Truth. So the warrior set out into the world on a quest for Truth. He went to temples and monasteries, to mountaintops where sages meditated, to remote forests where ascetics scourged themselves, but nowhere could he find Truth. Despairing one day and seeking shelter from a thunderstorm, he took refuge in a musty cave. There was an old crone there, a hag with matted hair and warts on her face, the skin hanging loose from her bony limbs, her teeth yellow and rotting, her breath malodorous. But as he spoke to her, with each question she answered, he realized he had come to the end of his journey: she was Truth. They spoke all night, and when the storm cleared, the warrior told her he had fulfilled his quest. ‘Now that I have found Truth,’ he said, ‘what shall I tell them at the palace about you?’ The wizened old creature smiled. ‘Tell them,’ she said, ‘tell them that I am young and beautiful.', 2836, 0), (138076, 'I had seen the world as either white or black.It is only when I read the pages of her diary that I understood why the sky looked so grey.', 5935, 0), (138077, 'In reality, love is fluid; it’s a verb, not a noun.', 124, 0), (138078, 'We always talk about our feelings, neglecting the important matters that have to be look over.', 14377, 0), (138079, 'Where our thoughts dwell, so becomes our reality. Choose wisely!', 9426, 0), (138080, 'And since the portions of both the large and the small are equal in amount, in this way too all things would be in everything; nor can they be separate, but all things have a portion of everything. Since there cannot be a smallest, nothing can be separated or come to be by itself, but as in the beginning now too all things are together. But in all things there are many things, equal in amount, both in the larger and the smaller of the things being separated off.', 26173, 0), (138081, 'When we use words like biophotonic matrix, we rarely consider a word can be a reality in itself...', 7581, 0), (138082, 'Reality is not a thought experiment.', 14676, 0), (138083, 'We imagine all these postapocalyptic, class-stratified, new-world-order techno-futures. But actually the real world, the world we live in, this is the dystopia.', 15904, 0), (138084, 'How good it is when you have roast meat or suchlike foods before you, to impress on your mind that this is the dead body of a fish, this is the dead body of a bird or pig; and again, that the Falernian wine is the mere juice of grapes, and your purple edged robe simply the hair of a sheep soaked in shell-fish blood!And in sexual intercourse that it is no more than the friction of a membrane and a spurt of mucus ejected. How good these perceptions are at getting to the heart of the real thing and penetrating through it, so you can see it for what it is!This should be your practice throughout all your life: when things have such a plausible appearance, show them naked, see their shoddiness, strip away their own boastful account of themselves.Vanity is the greatest seducer of reason: when you are most convinced that your work is important, that is when you are most under its spell.', 267, 0), (138085, 'The day is coming when your vision will become a reality', 3800, 0), (138086, 'You have to shelf your excitement and be realistic about your internal and external strengths and weaknesses. (p.70)', 11349, 0), (138087, 'We live in a world of banal miracles.', 26174, 0), (138088, 'Immerse yourself into self-development, realization of potential and establishing yourself as real person and personality', 3800, 0), (138089, 'The Lord can cause a vision to turn into reality', 3800, 0), (138090, 'There is nothing more real than light.', 7602, 0), (138091, 'The bright the light is, the darker the shadows are.', 20493, 0), (138092, 'In reality, commissions rarely solve complicated problems. Therefore, the following question arises: what is worse – to establish a commission knowing it cannot solve a complicated problem, or to believe that the commission will truly solve such a problem?', 3094, 0), (138093, 'We live with the key purpose of receiving the approval of those around us because we don’t know who we are in reality', 3800, 0), (138094, 'Then, without postponing anything, build a structure that will allow you to transform this vision into reality', 3800, 0), (138095, 'Love is the suspension of reality in favor of the sublime.', 6353, 0), (138096, 'On a subatomic level, it is not possible to determine where anything begins or ends, because there is no true separation of individual energy despite the illusions of the physical realities.', 20468, 0), (138097, 'The real acts of a real devil you know have been made acceptable by the fictitious actions of a nonexistent devil that you do not know.', 9447, 0), (138098, 'Public-sector employment — another way to be shielded from reality.', 9447, 0), (138099, 'If one is fooled by magic, then isn''t the magic as good as real?', 6359, 0), (138100, 'It doesn''t matter which line you walk, it''s gray just like any other', 7503, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (138101, 'There is no victor in life - for it is a game of expression, not of greed.', 7503, 0), (138102, 'Of everything we must first ask: is it real or not?', 9447, 0), (138103, 'This is one of the problems with reality: the extent to which it resembles bad fiction.', 13736, 0), (138104, 'Just as terror, even in its pre-total, merely tyrannical form ruins all relationships between men, so the self-compulsion of ideological thinking ruins all relationships with reality. The preparation has succeeded when people have lost contact with their fellow men as well as the reality around them; for together with these contacts, men lose the capacity of both experience and thought. The ideal subject of totalitarian rule is not the convinced Nazi or the convinced Communist, but people for whom the distinction between fact and fiction (i.e., the reality of experience) and the distinction between true and false (i.e., the standards of thought) no longer exist.', 2694, 0), (138105, 'Human beings intuitively divide time into the past, the present, and the future. We perceive the past as immutable and fixed, the present as reflecting actuality, and the future as undefined and nebulous. As time passes, the moment that was once was part of the present becomes part of the past; and a moment of the heretofore previously unrealized future arrives and becomes the new present. The past is a record, the present is real, and the future is an imaginary thought.', 2764, 0), (138106, 'Our reality is a blend of the impossible becoming possible.', 7501, 0), (138107, 'Based upon quantum mechanics, our physical reality should not be solid. Most likely our physical reality is an elaborate illusion within our own consciousness and the collective consciousness of the Universe/God.', 20468, 0), (138108, 'We all want to be the hero but some of us are born to be villains and side characters.', 26175, 0), (138109, 'We are too scared to be real!',