ss.', 26320, 0), (138962, 'Spirit means Breath and without one or the other there is no life.', 22490, 0), (138963, 'For all the pain I saw at Paterson, it is nothing compared to the pain that people inflict upon each other in the real world. All I can think of now is that it is not right for me to be unaware of that pain, including the pain that I inflict on others. Only how is it possible to live without being either numb to it or overwhelmed by it?', 22086, 0), (138964, 'Every language has its own word for the sun, but the sun us always the same.', 884, 0), (138965, 'The volume of your muscles doesn''t make you a good husband. The way you treat her does.', 26306, 0), (138966, 'The physical world exists, but that’s only the paint and canvas; that’s only the instrument we use to make music; that’s only the stage where the play is performed.', 23954, 0), (138967, 'Believe me...Nothing is bad or wrong , just prove it as right', 26321, 0), (138968, 'I''m A Speaker, Your A Listener. ', 26322, 0), (138969, 'Believe me...Nothing is bad, just prove it as right', 26321, 0), (138970, 'Ga thought about reminding the Dear Leader that they lived in a land where people had been trained to accept any reality presented to them.', 9853, 0), (138971, 'Among the books there were also some containing bombast. They didn''t try to portray Nature as it is within and outside of man; rather, they tried to make it more beautiful, seeking to elicit certain effects. I turned away from them. If reality isn''t sacred to them, how are they capable of creating something more beautiful than God''s Creation?', 6173, 0), (138972, 'The map of what we call reality is an ever-shifting mosaic of ideas.', 14449, 0), (138973, 'I know, I know: it can be frustrating as hell. But people have an unfortunate habit of assuming they understand the reality just because they understood the analogy. You dumb down brain surgery enough for a preschooler to think he understands it, the little tyke’s liable to grab a 